Text.Value: Friends? I've gathered quite the collection.
Gods, you're stubborn. Karlach's not a devil, and you know it.
I've tried to tell you - I'm not what you think I am.
Truce then, hey?

EditorData.NodeContext: A little bit of uncertainty, hoping Wyll is calming down

Text.Value: I'm asking you to live, Wyll. I don't want to hurt you. And, to be frank, I'd rather not find out how the Blade got his name.
Let's start at allies and work from there.
Karlach. The archdevil Zariel's gladiator, come to burn the Sword Coast to ash.
Proof, clear as summer sky. It's over, Karlach. It's time you feel the sting of the Blade.
Well I'll be godsdamned - the Blade of Frontiers. Thought I'd shaken you for good. That'll teach me to underestimate you.
I've hunted you to the Hells and beyond. It ends here, Karlach.
Don't you fucking dare.
I brought you your target, Wyll. Why don't you do the honours?
You don't know what this means. You don't know what you're asking me to do.

EditorData.NodeContext: Fighting with himself. He doesn't want to believe it. Not killing Karlach means punishment from Mizora

Text.Value: Too bad. I thought maybe you could be a friend. I could've done with one of those.
Thank the gods, he sees sense! Look, Blade - Wyll - I know you love bashing evil - we have that in common.
But I do. The Blade of Frontiers will be only a memory come tomorrow.
Shut it, devil - I know your kind. A heart darker than a shadow's nightmares. You'd cut a child's throat just to taste the blood.
Well - not counting the fuckers that need a good hurting.
Well I'll be godsdamned - the Blade of Frontiers. Thought I'd shaken you for good. That'll teach me to underestimate you.
Thank the gods. Thought I was going to have to take your head.

EditorData.NodeContext: Relieved Wyll is seeing sense. Calming down from her anger.

Text.Value: No. Devils can not be trusted!
It's over, 'Blade'.
Well, Wyll. I tried.
How can I make peace with the monster I was sent to kill?
The two of you have met before, I see.
You've got it all wrong, Wyll. Karlach's not about to hurt anyone.
*Wyll catches his breath, and his lips straighten. Sheer dread twists his face.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Wyll catches his breath, and his face hardens. Signs of worry, fear - even sheer dread.

EditorData.stateContext: Wyll is not in attack position.

Text.Value: *Two souls hang in the balance. Kill Karlach, fulfil your contract - and condemn a possible innocent to the Hells. Or spare her and face the repercussions with Mizora.*
To the Hells with you, then - and may you all forever burn.
You know monsters better than anyone. Can't you look in my eyes and see I'm not a devil?
I see you've met. Saves me the trouble of introductions.
Let's take things down a notch, shall we? She's no devil, Wyll. You'll have to look elsewhere to find fodder for your blade.
*A great fire roars through you - the fire of the First Hell.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands to temples, mindmeld is happening

Text.Value: You fight in the Blood War for Zariel. You'll bring the Blood War to the Coast.
Stand down. You saw what I saw - Karlach is not a danger.

EditorData.stateContext: Wyll  in aggressive, unarmed stance, ready to attack Karlach

Text.Value: *Another vision. Karlach's blade raised, slicing through devils - Zariel's servants - as her eyes dart around, seeking escape.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands to temples, mindmeld is happening

Text.Value: It will mean my undoing, but... I believe you.
If by 'met' you mean hoofing it through the Hells with this fucker on my tail.
Touchy, touchy. But hey, I spent a decade in Avernus surrounded by imps and devils. Winning you over will be child's play.
Fine, but he needs to stand down. We saw the truth for ourselves.
Aye. Truce.

EditorData.NodeContext: Resigned to his fate but knows he's making the right decision in not attacking Karlach.

Text.Value: Look, whatever else it may be, the tadpole isn't a liar. I never wanted to serve Zariel, and I escaped the first chance I could. So stand down.

EditorData.NodeContext: Ready for a fight if needed.

Text.Value: Friends it is.
How about we all take a nice deep breath and calm the fuck down. Just cause I want to live doesn't mean I want him dead.
Control yourself, Wyll. I understand bloodthirst. But this is no time to quench it.
I swear to you, on all I am, I'm not what you think.
Dammit. This is an unwelcome complication.
A devil? I didn't take the Blade for a fool. I'm - ngh!
Shit. Shit.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: There's a pause, and then Wyll swears. He realises he has resigned himself to becoming a devil himself. He's upset - but he knows he did the right thing. He relaxes into a neutral position.

Text.Value: If you'd just hear me out -
*A great fire roars through you - the fire of the First Hell.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands to temples, mindmeld is happening

Text.Value: And yet you served.
It's you I don't trust, Wyll. You wanted a fight? You've got it.
One horn. The stink of Avernus. Advocatus diaboli.
You saw the truth. I may be an effective soldier, but I never wanted to serve Zariel. Legged it away from her the first chance I got.
Easy, Wyll. She's no devil. There's no fight to be had here.
*Her rage and desperation seep into you. She is a victim of the Blood War, not an agent of it.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands to temples, mindmeld is happening

Text.Value: I see the good in you, Karlach. I promise not to lose sight of it, even when the Hells burn hottest.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[opening, face-to-face]

Wyll and Karlach stand facing one another, fists clenched.

Text.Value: I'm asking you to live, Wyll. I don't want to hurt you. And, to be frank, I'd rather not find out how the Blade got his name.
*You are Karlach, tearing through demons across a blood-red landscape of fire and volcanic cinder.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands to temples, mindmeld is happening

Text.Value: Now, now, children - let's not lose our heads. Figuratively or literally.

Text.Value: You saw Karlach's thoughts. She poses no threat to the Sword Coast.
*Wyll shudders with Karlach's desperation. She is a victim of the Blood War, not an agent of it.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands to temples, mindmeld is happening

Text.Value: Yeah, I stowed away on a mind flayer ship so I could bring the war home. Makes perfect sense.
You two have met before, I take it?

EditorData.stateContext: Karlach in aggressive, unarmed stance, ready to attack Wyll

Text.Value: If by 'met' you mean hoofing it through the Hells with this fucker on my tail.
For fuck's sake, you must be half troll to have a skull that thick.
Well met. Now let's kick some arse while there's still arse to be kicked.
Would you listen to sense? This doesn't have to end badly - for either of us.
I can live with that. Besides, I enjoy winning hard cases over.
You really are no devil, are you? I've... I've been deceived.
Fine, but he needs to stand down. We saw the truth for ourselves.
You know, I could've used a few friends. Pity that won't be any of you.
Save your breath. Let's see if this devil bleeds.
Fuck. I'll never get used to that.
I'm sorry, Karlach. There's too much at stake.
You two have met before, I take it?
By Balduran's helm, I - no. I will not be tricked!

EditorData.NodeContext: Questioning himself. He has learned the 'monster' he hunts is a victim, but he still ready to attack

Text.Value: You know monsters, right? Better than anyone. Look into my eyes. Can't you see I'm not what you think?
It's done, Karlach. By my living soul, you will forever burn.
You want a fight Wyll? I'll give you one.
I don't need more friends.
I should never have trusted you, Karlach. You're as good as dead.
My sources say otherwise. Not a devil? Prove it.
Be practical. She's infected, same as us. We need allies, not enemies.
Oh marvellous, you've already met.

EditorData.NodeContext: Realising Karlach and Wyll had met in the past (Wyll tried to kill Karlach)

Text.Value: You would've died in the attempt. But - there have been enough threats today.
You know, I could've used a few friends. Pity that won't be any of you.
No. No second-guessing. The devil dies - now.
How should I do that exactly? Carve out my soul to serve with a nice side of turnips?
You don't know what this means. You don't know what you're asking me to do.
I swear to you, on all I am, I'm not what you think.
Look - it's an honour to be chased by a famed hero. I'm no devil, though. Not by a long shot.
You're right. Let's cut her down before she causes any trouble.
*The front lines of the Blood War. With every swing of her axe, Karlach fulfils mistress Zariel's purpose.*
